{"word":"πιπράσκω","slug":"πιπράσκω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>πιπράσκω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:πιπράσκω'><el>πιπράσκω</el></a> <a href='S:shortened'>shortd.</a> from <el>πιπεράσκω</el>, <a href='S:reduplication'>redupl.</a> form of <a href='S:περάω'><el>περάω2</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to sell</i>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b>:— <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be sold</i>, <a href='S:especially'>esp.</a> for exportation, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, attic<p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to sell</i> for a bribe, of political leaders, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b>:—<a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> in <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <el>πέπραμαι</el> <i>I am bought and sold!</i> <a href='S:id est'>i. e.</a> <i>betrayed, ruined, undone</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}